\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -i
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This will allow you to select which mirror, or mirrors, to try when checking
 for software updates and downloading new packages.
 It's normally best to choose mirrors that are geographically close to you,
 so if you're in Canada then servers from Canada and the US are generally
 a good bet.
 Of course, you're free to choose whichever you want!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To reset back to an automatic choice, run this command:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -f
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Remember to force a download of the package lists to use the new mirrors!
